    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-09T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-09T14:00:00-05:00" n="54"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/2438: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-09T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 9, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>375. Your 529, May 8, 5 p.m. For your strictly confidential information only: We
                    concur in your opinion that nothing should be <pb facs="0056" n="46"
                        xml:id="pg_46"/> done in any way that might arouse the slightest suspicion
                    on the part of the Chinese of any lack of confidence in them and have
                    accordingly taken up the matter with General Marshall. He shares this view, and
                    it is understood that the War Department will immediately send appropriate
                    instructions in the matter to General Magruder.<note n="1" xml:id="d54fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
